defaultOne of the reasons for the decline in the uptake of home dialysis is thought to be the overestimation of the need to increase in-centre haemodialysis capacity
default which has resulted in a proliferation of centre based dialysis facilities throughout the UK.
default 
defaultOnce a centre has been commissioned, it is incumbent upon clinicians and managers to keep the facility working at capacity to ensure cost effectiveness.
default 
defaultHowever, decommissioning of such services and re-allocating staff to support home dialysis patients would greatly improve the ability for more people to be treated at home.
default&#xa0;
defaultAs well as the many quality of life benefits
default and improved outcomes
default that patients report by being on a home 
defaultbased treatment it
default also generates cost savings
default.
default 
defaultWith the current focus by the NHS on
default QIPP
default, to improve patient outcomes and generate cost savings these forms of treatment need to be fast tracked and implemented on a more substantial scale so that the full benefits can be realised by patients and the NHS alike.
